First room on the left,
that's my old room.

00:28.593 --> 00:30.639
Looks like
everything's still here.

00:30.682 --> 00:33.076
-It is?
-The Step Soldiers?

00:33.120 --> 00:35.948
TONI:
Oh, that was my old
high school dance squad.

00:35.992 --> 00:38.125
[laughs]
Hey...

00:38.168 --> 00:39.648
This quilt is pretty.

00:39.691 --> 00:41.345
Yeah. It's the only thing
I have of my mom's.

00:41.389 --> 00:43.043
She got deported
when I was 14.

00:43.086 --> 00:45.088
Who was that, uh,
pretty little reporter of yours?

00:45.132 --> 00:46.829
You want fucking Georgie
to kill somebody?

00:50.833 --> 00:54.315
TONI:
Whoever killed Wally knew him,

00:54.358 --> 00:56.404
and would have left a trail.

01:05.108 --> 01:08.329
Aw, just keep it in here
just in case...

01:11.506 --> 01:14.465
[indistinct chatter]

01:27.174 --> 01:28.131
LULU [shouting]:
She did it!

01:28.175 --> 01:31.134
[laughs, sighs]

01:31.178 --> 01:32.744
You fixed it.

01:32.788 --> 01:34.703
-She fixed the copy machine!
-[scattered cheers]

01:34.746 --> 01:37.314
-God, a lifesaver. Thank you.
-Thank you.

01:37.358 --> 01:38.533
-Hey.
-Hi.

01:38.576 --> 01:40.404
I wanted to apologize.

01:40.448 --> 01:42.711
No, I'm the one who
should be apologizing.

01:42.754 --> 01:46.671
That's true. But, Beth,
all is forgiven because

01:46.715 --> 01:48.238
I didn't even need Tuna.

01:48.282 --> 01:51.023
-Didn't you hear?
-No.

01:51.067 --> 01:53.852
The podcast debut just made
New and Noteworthy.

01:53.896 --> 01:56.638
We have optimal
home page visibility,

01:56.681 --> 01:58.422
unprecedented feedback signals,

01:58.466 --> 02:01.512
and listenership is already
converting to subscription.

02:02.774 --> 02:04.689
I feel like I'm not making
sense, but I know that I am.

02:04.733 --> 02:07.953
No, no, you are, you are.
That's great.

02:07.997 --> 02:09.912
-Congrats.
-Thanks.

02:09.955 --> 02:12.436
Yeah, don't even worry
about slapping me in the face.

02:12.480 --> 02:14.395
Oh, yeah. No, yeah.

02:14.438 --> 02:15.874
Thanks for being
so cool about that.

02:15.918 --> 02:19.487
Um, listen.
So how's it going with Toni?

02:19.530 --> 02:22.403
Oh, uh, yeah, um, great.

02:22.446 --> 02:24.796
I'm just-- I'm trying to take
a little step back.

02:24.840 --> 02:27.321
You know, not-not rush
to any conclusions.

02:27.364 --> 02:29.149
-So...
-Oh. Beth...

02:29.192 --> 02:30.715
Toni did it.

02:30.759 --> 02:32.108
What?

02:32.152 --> 02:33.631
[whispers]:
Why would you say that?

02:33.675 --> 02:35.677
Because I know what it's like
to be a woman

02:35.720 --> 02:37.722
and to be afraid of a man.

02:37.766 --> 02:39.855
Boxed in by fear

02:39.898 --> 02:42.901
and feeling like violence
is the only way out.

02:42.945 --> 02:44.947
I know what it's like
to kill a man.

02:44.990 --> 02:47.689
-I amToni.
-Okay, Toni's her own person...

02:47.732 --> 02:48.951
-Who's just like me.
-No.

02:48.994 --> 02:50.431
Who also killed someone.

02:50.474 --> 02:51.867
Stop! She did not!

02:51.910 --> 02:53.825
Okay, you know what, Beth?

02:53.869 --> 02:57.133
-[sighs]
-I know that you have
a lot riding on her innocence,

02:57.177 --> 02:59.962
but deep down, there's a part
of you that knows I'm right.

03:00.963 --> 03:03.139
Just trust your gut.

03:03.183 --> 03:05.533
That's what I did,
and it saved my life.

03:05.576 --> 03:07.535
And got me a book deal.

03:07.578 --> 03:09.928
And, like,
a shit-ton of new sponsors.

